<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-562-921  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 562 921.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>DG Review  Oct 1990 v11 n4 p20(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Play it safe. (security plan)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Trent, Gloria.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A single security system is not sufficient to protect a system.andO;There are eight categories of security products and services:services, including buying disaster recovery services oroutsourcing day-to-day security; awareness and training, includingtraining packages, books, and VCR tapes; decision support; systemaccess control; physical security; computer operations, whichneeds software that can recover a data base and bring the systemback up if there is a disk read/write crash; backup and disasterrecovery, including remote hot sites, archival storage of data,and data recovery software; and communications security, such asencryption of sensitive data and message authentication.andP;  Hardwareprovides a higher degree of protection, but is difficult to modifyor customize.andP;  Software may be circumvented by sophisticatedprogrammers.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     SecurityDisaster PlanningHardwareSoftware.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>